headline: Stocks Set for Muted Open After Trump’s Tariff Threats, Big Tech Earnings and Fed Meeting in Focus
summary: March S&P 500 E-Mini futures (ESH26) are down -0.05%, and March Nasdaq 100 E-Mini futures (NQH26) are down -0.14% this morning, pointing to a muted open on Wall Street as President Trump’s tariff threats against Canada and the looming risk of a partial U.S. government shutdown curbed risk appetite at the start of a busy week.

headline: Will Industrial Restocking and Dividend Stability Change Texas Instruments' (TXN) Embedded AI Supply-Chain Narrative?
summary: Texas Instruments’ board previously declared a quarterly cash dividend of US$1.42 per share, payable on February 10, 2026, to shareholders of record as of January 30, 2026, while analysts have recently highlighted an industrial restocking cycle and improving demand across its key semiconductor end markets. These developments underscore how Texas Instruments’ large exposure to industrial customers and embedded processing could influence how investors view its role in broader AI and...
